The weight accorded to an individual patient’s goals of care diminishes in light of the community’s increased need for health care resources.
Doctors are trying to assess who will benefit the most for the longest when they offer access to scarce medical resources.
Each community member can be involved in their own health care by educating themselves about advance care directives.
Health care proxies should be signed and personal values that inform choices for medical care should be discussed with family members.
Stevens: For Christians in health care in particular, you’ve really got to dig into God’s Word.